## Certificate transactions

> Headers

```
Content-type: application/json
```

> Body example

```json
{
    "shop_id": "...",
    "shop_secret": "...",
}
```

> Request example

```shell
curl https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/:code/transactions?shop_id=...&shop_secret=...
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "payload": [
    {
      "id": 333746,
      "amount": -300,
      "event": "order",
      "order_id": "773",
      "identifier": "",
      "product_id": "17"
    },
    {
      "id": 333746,
      "amount": 100,
      "event": "refund",
      "order_id": "773",
      "identifier": "",
      "product_id": "17"
    }
  ]
}
```

Returns certificate's transactions history

### HTTP Request


`GET https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/:code/transactions`
### Query Parameters

| Parameter   | Required | Description                                                         |
|-------------|----------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| shop_id     | true     | Your API key                                                        |
| shop_secret | true     | Your API secret key                                                 |





